<org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-viRhmCjT3H-vrro7MLUzhA" name="meth_user_guidelines,_IaVnQCMuEd-VobohmWswkw" guid="-viRhmCjT3H-vrro7MLUzhA" changeDate="2011-07-27T11:59:32.171-0700" version="7.5.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact&amp;nbsp;is a &quot;how-to&quot; manual for an organization's method library. Aside from describing the basics of how&#xD;
    teams access and use the deployed method assets, this artifact includes policies for tailoring the assets to meet the&#xD;
    needs of individual projects -&amp;nbsp;this allows teams to comply with the intent and purpose of the organization's&#xD;
    method assets in a manner that is consistent with their own&amp;nbsp;projects' constraints, environment and&#xD;
    objectives.&amp;nbsp;This artifact&amp;nbsp;ensures teams are not over-burdened with unnecessary or unproductive activities.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Typical&amp;nbsp;examples of method asset tailoring&amp;nbsp;include:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Modifying the lifecycle model (for example&amp;nbsp;phases and&amp;nbsp;milestones).&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Modifying work products or tasks content.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Changing the order in which tasks are performed.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Balance the need for consistently applying processes with allowing flexibility for project teams. Consider variables&#xD;
    such as project scale, team maturity, and technical domain, which can impact both the type and formality of the process&#xD;
    needed.&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact helps&amp;nbsp;project teams identify, access, and use&amp;nbsp;the right set of method assets for their&#xD;
    projects. It also supports consistent process application across the organization to ensure that applicable standards&#xD;
    are met and objectives are achieved.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>Without this artifact, method assets may be used inconsistently across the organization.&amp;nbsp;Results cannot be monitored&#xD;
to determine if process improvements are helping the organization meet its identified objectives.</impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact is not needed when:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        The organization has no standard method library or method assets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Only one set of assets is available, and it&amp;nbsp;is used &quot;as-is&quot; with no tailoring&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></reasonsForNotNeeding>
  <briefOutline>&lt;p>&#xD;
    This artifact typically contains the following sections:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Overview of available assets and their usage&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Instructions for accessing the method assets&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Guidance for tailoring and extending the method assets using method authoring tools&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Policies for tailoring, including any required approvals&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></briefOutline>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:ArtifactDescription>
